      <description>The miners’ 1972 strike against Duke Power Company over working conditions, wages, and labor practices inspired the award-winning documentary "Harlan County, USA." The miners struck to join United Workers of America, hoping to improve their jobs and lives. Their wives’ support proved critical to sustaining the strike over thirteen months. Corn’s images for The Tennessean humanized the miners.</description>
